From: Christoph Hellwig <hch@lst.de>
Date: Mon, 4 May 2020 14:47:56 +0200
Subject: bdi: add a ->dev_name field to struct backing_dev_info
Git-commit: 6bd87eec23cbc9ed222bed0f5b5b02bf300e9a8d
Patch-mainline: v5.7-rc5
References: bsc#1171844

Cache a copy of the name for the life time of the backing_dev_info
structure so that we can reference it even after unregistering.

Fixes: 68f23b89067f ("memcg: fix a crash in wb_workfn when a device disappears")
Reported-by: Yufen Yu <yuyufen@huawei.com>
Signed-off-by: Christoph Hellwig <hch@lst.de>
Reviewed-by: Jan Kara <jack@suse.cz>
Reviewed-by: Bart Van Assche <bvanassche@acm.org>
Signed-off-by: Jens Axboe <axboe@kernel.dk>
Acked-by: Jan Kara <jack@suse.cz>
---
 include/linux/backing-dev-defs.h |    1 +
 include/linux/backing-dev.h      |    2 +-
 mm/backing-dev.c                 |    3 ++-
 3 files changed, 4 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

--- a/include/linux/backing-dev-defs.h
+++ b/include/linux/backing-dev-defs.h
@@ -194,6 +194,7 @@ struct backing_dev_info {
 	wait_queue_head_t wb_waitq;
 
 	struct device *dev;
+	char dev_name[64];
 	struct device *owner;
 
 	struct timer_list laptop_mode_wb_timer;
--- a/include/linux/backing-dev.h
+++ b/include/linux/backing-dev.h
@@ -508,7 +508,7 @@ static inline const char *bdi_dev_name(s
 {
 	if (!bdi || !bdi->dev)
 		return bdi_unknown_name;
-	return dev_name(bdi->dev);
+	return bdi->dev_name;
 }
 
 #endif	/* _LINUX_BACKING_DEV_H */
--- a/mm/backing-dev.c
+++ b/mm/backing-dev.c
@@ -876,7 +876,8 @@ int bdi_register_va(struct backing_dev_i
 	if (bdi->dev)	/* The driver needs to use separate queues per device */
 		return 0;
 
-	dev = device_create_vargs(bdi_class, NULL, MKDEV(0, 0), bdi, fmt, args);
+	vsnprintf(bdi->dev_name, sizeof(bdi->dev_name), fmt, args);
+	dev = device_create(bdi_class, NULL, MKDEV(0, 0), bdi, bdi->dev_name);
 	if (IS_ERR(dev))
 		return PTR_ERR(dev);
 
